"title": "5339: home",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5339",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The place of origin or residence, to which people feel attached and where they belong. The term is used of houses, towns, lands and in various figurative and spiritual senses.</p>\n<h2>Divine blessing upon homes</h2>\n<h3>It brings peace and security</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa32:18\">ISA 32:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs13:5\">2KI 13:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps127:1-Ps127:2\">PSA 127:1–127:2</a></p>\n<h3>It is promised to the righteous</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov3:33\">PRO 3:33</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov12:7\">PRO 12:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov14:11\">PRO 14:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov15:6\">PRO 15:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov24:3-Prov24:4\">PRO 24:3–24:4</a></p>\n<h3>It is granted because of a godly presence</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam6:11\">2SA 6:11</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr13:14\">1CH 13:14</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen30:27-Gen30:30\">GEN 30:27–30:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen39:4-Gen39:5\">GEN 39:4–39:5</a></p>\n<h2>Human affection for homes</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam19:37\">2SA 19:37</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen31:30\">GEN 31:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num10:29-Num10:30\">NUM 10:29–10:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth1:6-Ruth1:18\">RUT 1:6–1:18</a> <em>Ruth's loyalty to Naomi is stronger than her attachment to her homeland</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam7:17\">1SA 7:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job29:18\">JOB 29:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps102:13-Ps102:14\">PSA 102:13–102:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps137:1-Ps137:6\">PSA 137:1–137:6</a></p>\n<h2>Instructions for home life</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut6:6-Deut6:9\">DEU 6:6–6:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut20:5-Deut20:8\">DEU 20:5–20:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut24:5\">DEU 24:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph6:1-Eph6:4\">EPH 6:1–6:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:18-Col4:1\">COL 3:18–4:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim5:4\">1TI 5:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim5:8\">1TI 5:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim5:11-1Tim5:14\">1TI 5:11–5:14</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus2:4-Titus2:5\">TIT 2:4–2:5</a></p>\n<h2>Homes as places of hospitality</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen29:13-Gen29:14\">GEN 29:13–29:14</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg19:18-Judg19:21\">JDG 19:18–19:21</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs4:8-2Kgs4:10\">2KI 4:8–4:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:25-John19:27\">JHN 19:25–19:27</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phlm1:22\">PHM 1:22</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb13:2\">HEB 13:2</a></p>\n<h2>Israel's home in Canaan</h2>\n<h3>It is promised to them</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam7:10-2Sam7:11\">2SA 7:10–7:11</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr17:9-1Chr17:10\">1CH 17:9–17:10</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod6:8\">EXO 6:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num14:30\">NUM 14:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps78:55\">PSA 78:55</a></p>\n<h3>It was taken from them</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs17:22-2Kgs17:23\">2KI 17:22–17:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs25:21\">2KI 25:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs17:5-2Kgs17:6\">2KI 17:5–17:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs18:10-2Kgs18:11\">2KI 18:10–18:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr36:20-2Chr36:21\">2CH 36:20–36:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps79:6-Ps79:7\">PSA 79:6–79:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel3:6\">JOL 3:6</a></p>\n<h3>It was restored to them</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zeph3:20\">ZEP 3:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek36:8\">EZK 36:8</a></p>\n<h2>Homes for animals</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job39:5-Job39:6\">JOB 39:5–39:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps84:3\">PSA 84:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps104:17-Ps104:18\">PSA 104:17–104:18</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov30:26-Prov30:28\">PRO 30:26–30:28</a></p>\n<h2>Homes in Jesus Christ's ministry</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:58\">LUK 9:58</a> <em>Jesus Christ had no permanent home.</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:38-Luke10:42\">LUK 10:38–10:42</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke14:1\">LUK 14:1</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark5:18-Mark5:20\">MRK 5:18–5:20</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:38-Luke8:39\">LUK 8:38–8:39</a> <em>The healed demoniac is sent back to his home town and family to be a witness.</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:11-Matt10:14\">MAT 10:11–10:14</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:10-Mark6:11\">MRK 6:10–6:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:4-Luke9:5\">LUK 9:4–9:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:5-Luke10:7\">LUK 10:5–10:7</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt19:29\">MAT 19:29</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:29-Mark10:30\">MRK 10:29–10:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:29-Luke18:30\">LUK 18:29–18:30</a></p>\n<h2>Homelessness</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor4:11\">1CO 4:11</a> <em>Paul had no permanent home</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job24:1-Job24:12\">JOB 24:1–24:12</a> <em>the suffering of the homeless</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:8-Heb11:10\">HEB 11:8–11:10</a> <em>People of faith do not see this world as their final home.</em></p>\n<h2>Home in a spiritual and figurative sense</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:2\">JHN 14:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:23\">JHN 14:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job17:13-Job17:15\">JOB 17:13–17:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl12:5\">ECC 12:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke16:9\">LUK 16:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:1-2Cor5:10\">2CO 5:1–5:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet3:13\">2PE 3:13</a></p>",
